item.title: Boeing 747’s touching final finish
item.description: The Boeing 747’s farewell flight is forming the shape of the iconic Qantas kangaroo in the air.

item.title: $A to rise with improved Chinese economy
item.description: Forecast double digit growth in the Chinese economy has prompted Westpac’s chief economist Bill Evans to believe the Australian dollar will continue to rise for the remainder of the year.

item.title: Tsunami warning for parts of US
item.description: A 7.8-magnitude earthquake that struck off the Alaskan peninsula has triggered a tsunami warning for areas within 300km of the epicentre, including parts of the US.

item.title: Share market dips amid COVID rise
item.description: Local sharemarkets dipped on Wednesday as fresh fears of a second COVID-19 wave were realised following a jump in the number of Victorian cases.

item.title: Dufty: I was scared I was done
item.description: St George Illawarra star Matt Dufty is the NRL’s form fullback, but six weeks ago he feared his career could be over if he didn’t perform.

item.title: The advice every parent needs to hear
item.description: Parents must learn how to use TikTok, Instagram and Snapchat to protect their children from online predators, Australia’s top cop says.

item.title: Melburnian fined for 100km surfing trip
item.description: A person attempting a 100km journey from Strathmore to the Surf Coast for a “surfing trip” was among 61 people fined in the past 24-hours for breaching lockdown laws in Victoria.

item.title: Rabbitoh Johnston on Storm radar
item.description: The Melbourne Storm have emerged as a candidate to sign unwanted South Sydney winger Alex Johnston with Fijian flyer Suliasi Vunivalu rugby union bound next season.

item.title: Sonny Bill won’t distract us: Cordner
item.description: Sydney Roosters captain Boyd Cordner says it won’t bother the back-to-back champions if Sonny Bill Williams chooses another club for his NRL comeback.

item.title: Melbourne City headed for Hunter
item.description: Melbourne City will make a welcome escape to NSW’s Hunter Region once their quarantine period is over to privately prepare for their A-League championship assault.
